article.headline: South Florida 86, St. Francis, NY 66
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Chris Howard scored 17 points and Dominique Jones added 14 as South Florida beat St. Francis, N.Y. 86-66 on Saturday. Howard went 7-of-8 inside the paint for the Bulls (8-4). St. Francis struggled offensively throughout the game, shooting just 33 percent from the field and going 6-of-13 from 3-point range. The Terriers (3-9) have lost six straight. South Florida, which has won eight of its last nine games, had four players score in double digits, including Adamu Saaka and Aaron Holmes, who both scored 13. Saaka was 5-of-6 from the field and hit two 3-pointers. The Bulls jumped out to a quick 12-4 lead in the first half, and led by 20 at halftime. South Florida hit nine 3-pointers in the game, while going 58 percent on field-goal shooting. The Terriers had three players score in double digits. Guard Jamaal Womack had a team-high 17 points, while Ricky Cadell and Robert Hines both had 10. South Florida center Kentrell Gransberry had a game-high 14 rebounds, 13 of them defensive.
